        {
          "reviewTitle": "Not great for long wear or covering imperfections",
          "reviewText": "I remember using this back when it first came out. I\u2019ve been using the Clinique stay matte foundation for years and it was recently discontinued so I decided to try this one again. First thing is that it pulls slightly orange (I used shade 122 for my light cool-toned skin), but not enough that it\u2019s super noticeable. I was surprised how good this looked on, it gave a very matte but natural finish with medium coverage. However, even with primer, concealer, setting powder and setting spray, it wears off after about 4 hours. I have acne and dark spots and after wearing this on several occasions for 4-8 hours all of the coverage disappeared. It is winter so it wasn\u2019t even a problem of sweating it off. My skin is oily but when it wears off my skin still looks pretty matte, it just loses the coverage. I might retry once my skin clears up but for now this is not for me.",
